==English==

===Etymology===
From {{prefix|en|re|live}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/ɹiːˈlɪv/}}
* {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Vealhurl-relive.wav|Audio (Southern England)}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[experience]] (something) again; to live over again. {{defdate|from 18th c.}}
#: {{ux|en|I '''relive''' that horrible accident every night and wake screaming.}}
#: {{ux|en|Replays in video games allow you to '''relive''' your greatest moments.}}
# {{lb|en|obsolete|transitive}} To bring back to life; to [[revive]], [[resuscitate]]. {{defdate|16th|17th c.}}
#* {{RQ:Spenser Faerie Queene|III|iv|passage=Had she not beene devoide of mortall slime, / Shee should not then have bene '''relyv'd''' againe [...].}}
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To come back to life.

